ing while hunting the light and prohibited  zoneplugging while the 'anti' guilds would resort to the lowest of tactics (exploits) to kill us.  <br>
   I think it comes down to personal ethics.  You know what you are doing when you kill someone before they can move or use any of the other lower tactics or exploits.   I find that the anonymity of the game really lowers inhibitions and tests the moral fiber of your fellow gamer.   <br>
   So there will always be cool people and bastards.  I treat the bastards as I feel they deserve to be treated (when I'm empowered to) and I try to game with the cool people I meet.  It doesn't really matter if it's honourable for someone to corpsecamp me or zone camp me but it's a fact of life on Sullon and if it's something that is really going to bother you, then the Zeks will be a rough place to live.  I just think it makes it more of a challenge.<br>
